"title": "5288: dead, the",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5288",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Human beings who have died. Scripture provides illustrations of the manner in which the dead are to be buried, as well as explaining the doctrines of resurrection and judgment.</p>\n<h2>Preparation of the dead for burial</h2>\n<h3>Washing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:37\">ACT 9:37</a></strong> <em>A custom common to both Jews and Greeks.</em></p>\n<h3>Embalming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:12\">MAT 26:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:2\">GEN 50:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:26\">GEN 50:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:14\">2CH 16:14</a></p>\n<h3>Grave clothes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:44\">JHN 11:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:46\">MRK 15:46</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:59\">MAT 27:59</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:40\">JHN 19:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:7\">JHN 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:6\">ACT 5:6</a></p>\n<h2>Provision for the dead</h2>\n<h3>Burial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:29-Gen49:30\">GEN 49:29–49:30</a></strong> <em>It was the normal practice for the people of God to be buried.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:30\">JOS 24:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:15\">1KI 11:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:2\">ACT 8:2</a></p>\n<h3>Cremation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:25\">JOS 7:25</a></strong> <em>Cremation was not a Hebrew practice, except in cases of difficulty.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:12\">1SA 31:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:10\">AMO 6:10</a></p>\n<h2>The plight of the unburied dead</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:2\">PSA 79:2</a></strong> <em>To be unburied was a disgrace, a mark of judgment.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl6:3\">ECC 6:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:19\">ISA 14:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:33\">JER 7:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:6\">JER 16:6</a></p>\n<h2>Personal contact with a dead body conferred uncleanness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:11\">NUM 19:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:11\">LEV 21:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:6\">NUM 6:6</a></p>\n<h2>The place of the dead</h2>\n<h3>Sheol and Hades</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:16\">EZK 31:16</a></strong> <em>Sheol is the OT term for the place of the dead; a grave, an underworld, a pit. Hades is the NT equivalent.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:26\">2KI 21:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:3-Ps88:4\">PSA 88:3–88:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:48\">PSA 89:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:3\">PSA 116:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:10\">ECC 9:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:9-Isa14:10\">ISA 14:9–14:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:31\">ACT 2:31</a></p>\n<h3>A place of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:13-Ps49:14\">PSA 49:13–49:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:17\">PSA 31:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:3-Ps88:5\">PSA 88:3–88:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:14\">NAM 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:22\">MAT 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:23\">MAT 11:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:15\">LUK 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:18\">MAT 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:13-Rev20:14\">REV 20:13–20:14</a></p>\n<h3>A place of deliverance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:8\">PSA 139:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:10\">PSA 16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:3\">PSA 30:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:13\">PSA 86:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:20\">PSA 107:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:14\">HOS 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:2\">JON 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:27\">ACT 2:27</a></p>\n<h2>The plight of the dead outside of Christ</h2>\n<h3>Physical death is the result of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:23\">ROM 6:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:17\">GEN 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:20\">EZK 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:32\">ROM 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:6\">ROM 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:15\">JAS 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>Final judgment will follow resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></strong> <em>The “second death” is the throwing of the lost into the lake of fire.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:28\">MAT 10:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41\">MAT 25:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:16-1John5:17\">1JN 5:16–5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:12\">JUD 1:12</a></p>\n<h2>Promises to the dead in Christ</h2>\n<h3>Death is but a sleep</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:13-1Thess4:14\">1TH 4:13–4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:11-John11:14\">JHN 11:11–11:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:17-1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:17–15:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:51-1Cor15:53\">1CO 15:51–15:53</a></p>\n<h3>Death has no hold on believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:51\">JHN 8:51</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:25-John11:26\">JHN 11:25–11:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a></p>\n<h3>Believers will be delivered from the second death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:11\">REV 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:6\">REV 20:6</a></p>",
